  "texts": [
    "For normal X-rays of KUB, the model correctly identified 1556 X-rays as normal (true negatives) and erroneously labeled 41 X-rays as kidney stones (false negatives).",
    "Table 4 illustrates the statistical significance of each criterion for the modified version of the VGG16, including accuracy, misclassification rate, precision, sensitivity, specificity, FPR, FNR, and F1 Score.",
    "8) F1 Score = 2 * Precision*Sensitivity Precision + Sensitivity Vol.",
    ":(0123456789) Scientific Reports | (2024) 14:6173 | https://doi.org/10.1038/s41598-024-56478-4",
    "www.nature.com/scientificreports/ Employing the LRP technique on the modified VGG16 model allowed us to pinpoint the regions in the KUB X-ray image that significantly contribute to the model's prediction of kidney stone presence."
